"{\"uid\": \"dailypost.ng-2024-07-04-messi-excluded-from-argentinas-squad-for-2024-olympics\", \"text\": \"Published  on  By  Inter Miami superstar, Lionel Messi, has been left out of Argentina's squad for the 2024 Olympics.  Chelsea midfielder, Enzo Fernandez, does not make the cut too.  However, Manchester City's Julian Alvarez will be heading to Paris.  Messi, who won an Olympic gold medal in Beijing in 2008, has been excused from international duty in Paris to manage his workload.  The 37-year-old is currently playing at the Copa America in the United States, where the Albiceleste are through to the quarter-finals.  Without Messi, Javier Mascherano has called up goalkeeper Geronimo Rulli, Nicolas Otamendi, and Alvarez for the summer games as the overage picks.  Chelsea have refused to give Fernandez permission to travel to France and the midfielder will join Enzo Maresca and the rest of his team mates for preseason.  Troost-Ekong returns to action for PAOK after lengthy injury layoff  Transfer: Williams leaves Chelsea to join new club  Messi needs help - Gomez tells Inter Miami's owner  UCL: Robert Lewandowski overtakes Messi, Ronaldo's record after scoring two goals for Barcelona  EPL: He glides past people like Messi - John Terry hails Arsenal star  UCL: Lamine Yamal outshines Messi, Ronaldo's record  LaLiga clears air on authorizing Messi's return to Barcelona  LaLiga: Why Messi will never return to Barcelona - Xavi  Copyright \\u00a9Daily Post Media Ltd\"}"